== English ==

A ''ley line'' is an imaginary straight line that links several prehistorical monuments: some amateur archeologists noticed that several sites were aligned, but there is no evidence that this was on purpose (such alignment ca be obtained by random placement). See the [[w:Ley line|Wikipedia article]].

